  "prompt": "Why did Apple change its name from Apple Computers Incorporated to Apple Inc?\"?",
  "response": "Apple changed its name from Apple Computer Incorporated to Apple Inc. in 2007 to reflect the company's shift in focus from solely computers to a broader range of consumer electronics and services. This change coincided with the launch of the first iPhone, marking Apple's entry into the mobile phone market. The new name, Apple Inc., better represented the company's expanded product lineup, which included devices like the iPod, iPhone, and later the iPad, as well as its growing emphasis on software and services like the iTunes Store and the App Store.",
